1.title: Man Killed, Pit Bull Shot, Goats Mauled?!; How Much Is a Stay-at-Home Mom Worth?
1.plot: A grieving widow rescues her deceased husband's dog only to have it accused of a deadly attack on a neighbor's pet goats; a man must consider the financial value of home care provided by his children's mother while he works full time.

9.title: Weave Rage Caught on Video!
9.plot: An angry mother gets physical at a beauty salon, claiming her teenage daughter's weave has been botched.

18.title: Gumption and Hustle Meat Pitch!; Apartment Heating by Oven?
18.plot: A salesman goes door-to-door and is offered a job by a fast friend, who sues him for $2000 shortly thereafter; a family being sued by their landlord claim they had no heat for months and were told that they were too stupid to figure it out.

31.title: Skin-Tight Prom Dress Splits Open?!
31.plot: A teenager demands thousands in damages for emotional distress after her hand-tailored prom dress rips on the big night.

40.title: Cheating, Drugs and Police?!; Obama Phone Hater?!
40.plot: A woman says she discovered that her boyfriend was cheating on her and doing drugs only a month after moving in with him; a phone for the financially-strapped goes missing and the suspected thief denies being resentful of the "free" phone.

42.title: Fast and Loose Friends?; Dog Rescue Fail?
42.plot: A young man claims he was trying to help out an abused mother of two, but she says he wanted more than friendship; Lady the shepherd becomes accused of attacking and biting a neighbor and her dog and traumatizing an autistic onlooker.

51.title: Penny-Pinching Millionaire Payback?!; Gay Ex-Lover in Hot Pursuit?!
51.plot: A woman claims she was in pain and heavily medicated when her millionaire ex-lover forced her to sign a promissory note; a man believes his ex-boyfriend staged their date to make another man jealous, leading to a 45-minute car chase.

65.title: Homeless Shelter Skirmish?!
65.plot: A homeless man diagnosed with stage IV cancer claims he was assaulted and thrown out of a shelter when a former friend accused him of theft.

72.title: World-Renowned Rapper Incident?!
72.plot: The failure of an A-list rapper to enter the United States leaves an investor and a promoter at odds when a concert falls through.

83.title: RV Turned Wine Bar Fail!; Father/Daughter Sting to Entrap Motorist?!
83.plot: A couple say a shoddy paint job stalled their dream of turning their 1952 antique RV into a wine bar; an uninsured, unlicensed motorist offers up a wild scenario to explain why he's not responsible for a crash.

84.title: Antique Watch Botch?; Beat Up Mercedes Bait & Switch?
84.plot: A small-business clock shop is accused of tearing apart a senior's prized anniversary pocket-watch; a struggling young man can't make payments on a used car.

86.title: Caught Floating in Pool by Police; Top Honors, Love and Lameness?!
86.plot: A 6-year-old testifies that his neighbor did not have permission to swim in his pool; the Judges try to mend a bitter feud between neighbors.

104.title: Love, Loans and Weight-Loss Surgery?!; Disabled Vet Loan Regret!
104.plot: A woman disagrees with her boyfriend's decision to have gastric bypass surgery, so he sues her for repayment of a loan; a disabled mom demands that her daughter's ex-lover pay back a $3,000 loan.

105.title: ATV Flip and Roll Disaster!; Hybrid Odometer Rollback?
105.plot: A teen who took an ATV for a ride, made a turn going 50 mph, and flipped and rolled is sued for damages; a woman accuses a man of fraud when the car she purchases breaks down after two days and has 200,000 more miles than advertised.

111.title: Crash Victim Robbed by Caregiver?!; Mom Stole My Wife's Wedding Ring?!
111.plot: A woman suffered a horrendous motorcycle accident, then may have been victimized by the friend who took her in; a woman sues her mother for the return of a wedding ring, and her mom tries to use an illegal recording as evidence against her.

124.title: Lemon Goes Up in Smoke?!; Stiffed by Deadbeat Friend?!
124.plot: A young woman hires a car broker to purchase a vehicle for her, then claims he delivered a car that was not drivable; a high school teacher makes the fateful mistake of rooming with a friend who has no intention of pitching in on rent.

127.title: Passenger Sings for Deliverance!
127.plot: A distraught passenger gets no relief from a reportedly abusive cabdriver who refuses to turn down the music or take directions.

128.title: Desperately Seeking Ling Ling the Pomeranian Puppy!; Storage Battle!
128.plot: A landlady accuses a former tenant of stealing her puppy when she vacated the premises; a restaurant owner claims a friend allowed a storage company to throw away his computer equipment.

129.title: Blown-Out Engine Scam?!; Judge Corriero's Dating Rules!
129.plot: After months of excuses, a woman is offered a used luxury car instead of her original vehicle; a man is shocked to discover that his best friend is dating his younger brother and is sued for repayment of a loan that he claims was a gift.
